cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with lexical analysis and semantic consistency in language. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses machine learning techniques such as random indexing and self-organizing maps. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with modeling word meaning and tracking semantic drifts in a large collection of text data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses AI techniques to analyze language data. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing a large collection of Amazon book reviews, which can be seen as a social network of sorts.
